{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017VH4LZWqSrCR4LUTcV8htb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logs stop after the node initialization - this means the ES nodes are stuck because they can't form the cluster without `cluster.initial_master_nodes`. In Elasticsearch 7.x, a new cluster requires `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to bootstrap. Without it, nodes can't elect a master and remain stuck in \"master not discovered yet\" state.\n\nThe problem is clear:\n1. The configmap has `discovery.seed_hosts` but is missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`\n2. ES 7.x requires `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to bootstrap a new cluster\n3. Once bootstrapped, this setting should be removed (it's bootstrap-only)\n4. I need to add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the ConfigMap, roll the StatefulSet to trigger bootstrap, then remove it once the cluster forms and do a final rolling restart to ensure stability without the bootstrap setting. So the plan is to update the ConfigMap with the bootstrap setting, do a rolling restart to let the cluster form, then remove that setting and restart again to confirm stability. Now I need to check what the Elasticsearch HTTP endpoint looks like through the services.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1523,"cache_read_input_tokens":38220,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1523},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5653ffbb-70be-4621-9489-d6750d1aea2c","uuid":"0308eb69-046e-4319-87c0-ab181a789b24","request_id":"req_011Ccfi7C6nuoFtKWqfhgYYP"}
