{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016DA6iMTw6AYXANYPGA6Sv2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals achieved. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The ConfigMap `es-config` was missing `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, which Elasticsearch 7.x requires to bootstrap a brand-new cluster. Without it, nodes discover each other via `discovery.seed_hosts` but have no quorum anchor — they loop forever on \"master not discovered yet\".\n\n**Fix sequence:**\n\n1. **Added `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** to the ConfigMap listing all 3 nodes, enabling ES to form the initial quorum and elect a master.\n\n2. **Rolling restart (round 1)** — deleted pods one at a time, each waited to be Ready before the next was touched. Cluster formed, reached yellow (3 nodes, master elected, 0 unassigned shards).\n\n3. **Removed `cluster.initial_master_nodes`** from the ConfigMap. Once the cluster state is persisted to disk, this setting is no longer needed — and leaving it in is dangerous (it can cause split-brain if a node subset tries to re-bootstrap after a full cluster wipe).\n\n4. **Rolling restart (round 2)** — verified the cluster stays **green** through every pod restart without the bootstrap setting. Result: `status=green`, 3 nodes, 0 unassigned shards, 100% active shards, master elected at `es-cluster-0`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1928,"cache_read_input_tokens":46613,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1928},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5653ffbb-70be-4621-9489-d6750d1aea2c","uuid":"f6a66f41-75fd-4099-ac0a-bf97aa44b51c","request_id":"req_011Ccfj9KaRJXSMnm4aJi1M4"}
